Okay, @AndriySvyryd, let's try this again. Sending you an invite...

@RDoser There is no need to use `[InverseProperty]` on both sides of the relationship and you don't need to use it at all when configuring it through Fluent API. In particular, if you remove the ones on `Holding.Investment` and `Investment.Holdings` the exception should go away.
Also, `EntityBase.MyIDProperty` references `Key` instead of `KeyAttribute`
